label: Roast Meatballs and Tomato-Tarragon Sauce
ingredientLines: 2 cups stale white/peasant style bread, cubed or torn
2 pounds ground lamb, meatloaf mix (equal parts ground pork, veal and sirloin) or ground turkey
About 1 cup, a couple of fat handfuls, freshly grated Pecorino
1 cup flat-leaf parsley tops and mint leaves combined, finely chopped
A fat drizzle of EVOO – Extra Virgin Olive Oil
1 tablespoon EVOO – Extra Virgin Olive Oil
1 28-ounce can San Marzano tomatoes, crushed by hand

label: Beef Bone Broth
ingredientLines: 4 pounds beef bones, preferably a mix of marrow bones and bones with a little meat on them, such as oxtail, short ribs, or knuckle bones (cut in half by a butcher)
2 medium unpeeled carrots, cut into 2-inch pieces
1 medium leek, end trimmed, cut into 2-inch pieces
6-quart (or larger) stockpot or a large slow cooker
